gress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"SessionStart\",\"hookName\":\"SessionStart:clear\",\"command\":\"cmux claude-hook session-start\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"c0a61f77-4017-429a-9160-9db30371463f\",\"toolUseID\":\"c0a61f77-4017-429a-9160-9db30371463f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T18:18:12.653Z\",\"uuid\":\"4e3641b4-c6dd-4f48-a4ad-4a4727b5b5b2\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"4e3641b4-c6dd-4f48-a4ad-4a4727b5b5b2\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"a6375286-82fb-48a9-90fd-f8e611e47d1b\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"snappy-yawning-swan\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"SessionStart\",\"hookName\":\"SessionStart:clear\",\"command\":\"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/hooks-handlers/session-start.sh\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"c0a61f77-4017-429a-9160-9db30371463f\",\"toolUseID\":\"c0a61f77-4017-429a-9160-9db30371463f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T18:18:12.653Z\",\"uuid\":\"c930abef-d8dc-4d1f-8763-e878711bdca2\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c930abef-d8dc-4d1f-8763-e878711bdca2\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"a6375286-82fb-48a9-90fd-f8e611e47d1b\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"snappy-yawning-swan\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Fix: Forward AWS SIGV4 env vars through tmux for Kiro E2E tests\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nAll Kiro E2E tests in CI fail with a login prompt timeout:\\n```\\nwaiting for kiro startup: timed out waiting for \\\"!>\\\" after 30s\\n--- pane content ---\\nYou are not logged in. Login now?\\n```\\n\\n**Root cause:** Kiro authenticates via AWS SIGV4 env vars (`AMAZON_Q_SIGV4`, `AWS_REGION`, `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID`, `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY`, `AWS_SESSION_TOKEN`). These are set in the Go test process but **don't propagate through tmux** — tmux sessions inherit the server's environment, not the client's. All other agents (Claude, Droid, Gemini) store credentials in files, so they aren't affected.\\n\\n**Existing pattern:** Claude Code's `StartSession` already solves this by wrapping the command with `env KEY=VALUE ...` (see `e2e/agents/claude.go:192-194`). Kiro needs to follow the same pattern.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### File: `e2e/agents/kiro.go` (only file modified)\\n\\n1. **Add `kiroAuthEnvArgs()` helper** — collects non-empty AWS auth env vars as `KEY=VALUE` strings\\n   ```go\\n   func kiroAuthEnvArgs() []string {\\n       var args []string\\n       for _, key := range []string{\\\"AMAZON_Q_SIGV4\\\", \\\"AWS_REGION\\\", \\\"AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID\\\", \\\"AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY\\\", \\\"AWS_SESSION_TOKEN\\\"} {\\n           if v := os.Getenv(key); v != \\\"\\\" {\\n               args = append(args, key+\\\"=\\\"+v)\\n           }\\n       }\\n       return args\\n   }\\n   ```\\n\\n2. **Update `RunPrompt()`** (line 141) — wrap kiro-cli command with `env`:\\n   ```go\\n   // Before:\\n   s, err := NewTmuxSession(name, dir, []string{\\\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY\\\"}, k.Binary(), args...)\\n\\n   // After:\\n   cmdArgs := append([]string{\\\"env\\\"}, kiroAuthEnvArgs()...)\\n   cmdArgs = append(cmdArgs, k.Binary())\\n   cmdArgs = append(cmdArgs, args...)\\n   s, err := NewTmuxSession(name, dir, []string{\\\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY\\\"}, cmdArgs[0], cmdArgs[1:]...)\\n   ```\\n\\n3. **Update `StartSession()`** (line 180) — same pattern:\\n   ```go\\n   // Before:\\n   s, err := NewTmuxSession(name, dir, []string{\\\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY\\\"}, k.Binary(), \\\"chat\\\", \\\"-a\\\", \\\"--agent\\\", \\\"entire\\\")\\n\\n   // After:\\n   cmdArgs := append([]string{\\\"env\\\"}, kiroAuthEnvArgs()...)\\n   cmdArgs = append(cmdArgs, k.Binary(), \\\"chat\\\", \\\"-a\\\", \\\"--agent\\\", \\\"entire\\\")\\n   s, err := NewTmuxSession(name, dir, []string{\\\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY\\\"}, cmdArgs[0], cmdArgs[1:]...)\\n   ```\\n\\n