 AWS vars aren't set, `kiroAuthEnvArgs()` returns nil. The command becomes `env kiro-cli chat ...`, which is equivalent to `kiro-cli chat ...` (POSIX standard behavior).\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint` — ensure code passes formatting and linting\\n2. `mise run test:ci` — run unit + integration tests\\n3. CI E2E tests with `--agent kiro` should now pass (Kiro receives the SIGV4 credentials)\\n\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"20e8a58a-f0d4-4415-9186-95e49d2f92be\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"a6375286-82fb-48a9-90fd-f8e611e47d1b\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"snappy-yawning-swan\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01VLkrabfU9Gns8Zi3biMJTj\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\n`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\\n**Why tmux doesn't forward env vars:** tmux sessions inherit the server process's environment, not the client's. When Go's `exec.Command` launches tmux, the env vars set in the test process don't propagate to the tmux pane. The `env KEY=VALUE cmd` pattern is the standard POSIX workaround — it explicitly sets vars in the command's environment.\\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`\\n\\nLet me read the file to implement the changes.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":19924,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":35259,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":19924},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYkPm6tVhi1BvbmMTkb4C\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"ec9fa3bb-cfa4-40f8-9055-cd1e352e90f0\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T18:18:18.639Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"ec9fa3bb-cfa4-40f8-9055-cd1e352e90f0\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"e